name: ExtensionRiskAssessment_Prediction
title: Cross-version Extension `R5.RiskAssessment.prediction` for use in FHIR R4
description: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `RiskAssessment.prediction` for use in FHIR R4.
purpose:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the
element `RiskAssessment.prediction` as defined in FHIR R5
in FHIR R4.

The source element is defined as:
`RiskAssessment.prediction` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:
*  R5: `RiskAssessment.prediction` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4B: `RiskAssessment.prediction` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4: `RiskAssessment.prediction` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Following are the generation technical comments:
Element `RiskAssessment.prediction` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `RiskAssessment.prediction`, but has no comparisons.

element.comment: Multiple repetitions can be used to identify the same type of outcome in different timeframes as well as different types of outcomes.
